<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06220009 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06220009 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  JUDGE; RULING; BANKRUPT; COURT; TRIAL; RETAIL; SALE; STORE; COMPANY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A federal bankruptcy judge Tuesday declared Mervyn's the victor in a smallbidding war over several Florida stores owned by Allied Stores Corp.;    JudgeJ. Vincent Aug, who is overseeing the bankruptcy proceedings related to thereorganization of Allied and Federated Department Stores Inc., approved theHayward-based chain's final $80 million cash offer for eight Jordan Marshstores.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JUDGE DECLARES MERVYN'S WINNER  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Last week, Dillard Department Stores Inc. entered a competing bid for thestores and four others, besting the initial $66 million offer of Mervyn's, adivision of Dayton Hudson Corp., by $8.5 million.;    During the hearing inCincinnati on Tuesday, Dillard increased its offer to $78.9 million in cashplus $1.1 million in indemnification on another Jordan Marsh store. ButMervyn's sweetened the bid to $80 million in cash for the eight stores. J.C.Penney Co. will buy one of the stores in the lot.;    Federated and Allied put20 stores operated by their Burdines and Maas Brothers/Jordan Marshsubsidiaries on the block as part of their business plan to emerge fromChapter 11 bankruptcy protection.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  New York Times  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910807  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  175  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday August 7, 199100220009,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>